[ti:Sueños lanzados - The Last of Us]
[ar:Unknown]
[length:02:34]
[la:en]

[00:10.20]In the shadows where I hide
[00:14.05]The silence whispers, never lied
[00:17.20]Deep inside, I'm holding tight
[00:21.95]This lingering pain won't take flight
[00:27.85]Still waters run deep, they say
[00:32.00]But here I wade through the gray
[00:36.80]This hurt I bear, a heavy load
[00:40.05]On this solitary, winding road
[00:45.95]Release the chains, let it go
[00:52.65]The tides will turn, ebb and flow
[00:55.65]Though it weighs upon my heart
[00:58.65]In letting go, I find a start
[01:04.55]I dream of paths where skies are clear
[01:10.50]Where courage rises, casting out fear
[01:16.45]In these dreams, I see a light
[01:19.80]Guiding me to make things right
[01:23.05]A world where hope is a gentle song
[01:28.55]Where every step is where I belong
[01:31.95]In this dreamscape, I find my place
[01:34.35]Awake or asleep, I embrace grace
[01:38.95]In the echoes of time we can't recall
[01:43.55]Are the moments that could have been magical
[01:47.85]A dance under stars that never shone
[01:51.60]A whispered promise never known
[01:54.95]The laughter in a night yet to begin
[01:57.70]A journey of us that might have been
[02:00.85]Now lost in dreams that never came true
[02:03.90]A tapestry of "what ifs" in hues
[02:06.78]In a moment of wreckless spite
[02:10.45]I sought vengeance under cold starlight
[02:13.20]The past haunted every restless night
[02:15.67]Till shadows danced with relentless fright
[02:19.05]Revenge was sweet, 'til it turned sour
[02:20.90]With guilt's heavy hand, came the hour
[02:23.60]Memories stain like a red, jagged scar
[02:25.55]The price of wrath, a wound forever ajar
